HEADWORD: Glaucus
<hw>Glau"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., sea
green.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of nudibranchiate
mollusks, found in the warmer latitudes, swimming in the open sea. These
mollusks are beautifully colored with blue and silvery white.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

